HEADWORD: Drawcansir
<hw>Draw"can*sir</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the name of
a bullying braggart character in the play by George Villiers called
⟦ldquo⟧The Rehearsal.⟦rdquo⟧]</ety> <def>A blustering, bullying fellow;
a pot-valiant braggart; a bully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The leader was of an ugly look and gigantic stature; he acted like
a <qex>drawcansir</qex>, sparing neither friend nor foe.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Draw-cut</ent>⟦br⟧
